volume.name: Bloke's Terrible Tomb of Terror Monster-Sized Collection

description:
Binky the space cat and his team of space pets are left at the vet's office while their humans are away. Binky plans an escape, only to stumble on a secret experiment that could give vicious aliens the upper hand! It's up to Binky and his friends to save the humans ... and themselves!

Binky: License to Scratch is the final book in the Binky Adventure series, where dry humour and sci-fi slapstick are mixed with lots of heart.
name: Binky: License to Scratch

description:
While London stood stolidly in the face of relentless Luftwaffe bombing attacks, petty criminal and expert safe-breaker Frank Raymond was on the run. He only stopped running when he enlisted in the Army.

Though Frank had joined up as a last-ditch, desperate attempt to save his life, he'd actually found his calling. He even went on to join a tough Special Forces unit - one which would soon have a use for his particular set of skills…
name: Fighting Frank

description:
He led his squadron into the thick of the fiercest dogfights - and yet he always came back without a scratch. He took fantastic risks, for he seemed to bear a charmed life.

They called him "Lucky" Lane, but even his own men came to hate and fear the young Squadron Leader, because they knew every time they took off, one of them would die. It wouldn't be Lane, though…for he wore the Tiger Ring…

Introduction

The cover of a compact graphic novel (for that's what Commando is, isn't it?) can do a number of things; illustrate a scene from the story, or a character or try to sum up everything in the story in a single image - like here. Over and above those things, though, the cover should most of all make you want to buy the book.

Ken Barr's artwork fulfils than function as much now as it did when it was first seen in 1965 by your then youthful editor. After all, you are going to buy the book, aren't you?

Calum Laird, Commando Editor

Note: Originally published as Commando No 148 (January 1965) and re-issues as No 767 (August 1973).
name: Sky Tiger

description:
They were a motley bunch - two Scotsmen, one Englishman, one Welshman, one Irishman and an Australian. Led by the unconventional Captain James Ramsey, they were known as the Special Raiding Force, and their job was to operate behind enemy lines in North Africa. They wrote their own rules, and their specially armed jeeps packed a real punch.

They were good at their job - very good - and the Germans had every reason to fear Ramsey's Raiders!

Introduction

I know this "By Special Request" issue is a bit earlier than usual but there are a number of good reasons for that. First, this story - the maiden Ramsey's Raiders tale - has had more requests for a fresh airing than any other book during my tenure as editor. As it's now ten years since the Raiders first broke cover, I reckoned it was time.

The second (and third, I suppose) reason is that we're going to issue a pair of brand-new Raiders adventures in the next couple of months so re-living their first raid is a great way to raise the curtain for new and seasoned readers alike.

Yes, that's right, a new pair of Raiders' stories is heading your way. You'll enjoy them, I know.

Calum Laird, Commando Editor

Note: Originally published as Commando No 3854 (October 2005).
name: Ramsey's Raiders

description:
When Captain Rod Tyler was sent to the war in Indo-China as a British observer with French forces, he found himself with the losing side in a savage guerrilla-style conflict. Not only that, he became piggy-in-the-middle between a bull-headed Foreign Legion officer and an alleged Nazi war criminal!

Just what had he let himself in for?

Introduction

What would happen if a soldier was convinced that one of his so-called comrades was a former war criminal but had no evidence to prove it?

That's the intriguing premise at the heart of this tough tale set during the war in Indochina. The French Foreign Legion's motto is "Honneur et Fidelite" (translated, perhaps, unsurprisingly, as "Honour and Fidelity") - and the story is about both of those things, where "fidelity" really means "loyalty" or "duty" as opposed to its modern meaning of "faithfulness".

So, then, Past Crimes is a fairly left field entry for Commando but it certainly works, thanks to Markham's script, veteran Denis McLoughlin's interior art and Ron Brown's emerald-hued cover.

Scott Montgomery, Deputy Editor
name: Past Crimes

description: Stranded in a strange Museum that's dedicated to him - and with no TARDIS in sight, the Doctor and Martha must make sence of their surroundings, hindered by one small fact - the Doctor has lost the memories of every one of his previous incarnations! With items relevant to each Doctor in their posession, the Doctor must try to use them to regain his memories before it's too late, starting with his earliest incarnation's memories, involving Susan, Barbara and Ian. This all-new sereis written by Tony Lee (Starship Troopers) features artist Pia Guerra in her first monthly comic since 'Y The Last Man'!
name: The Forgotten Part 1: Amputation

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Tenth Doctor Archives

description: Trapped in a strange museum and hunted by a gun-happy waxwork, an amnesiat Doctor must regain his memories of each of his incarnations - including a Second Doctor memory with Zoe and Jamie… and a Third Doctor remembrance with the Brigadier and Jo! But can he succeed before a familiar, bearded figure in the shadows kills him?
name: The Forgotten Part 2: Renewal

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Tenth Doctor Archives

description: With barely any of his memories complete and a rucksack of Nitro-9 their only defense, the Doctor and Martha try to locate the missing, believed-destroyed TARDIS. Meanwhile, the Doctor recovers more memories… are the stories trying to tell him something, and is everything really what it seems to be?
name: The Forgotten Part 3: Misdirection

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Tenth Doctor Archives

description: On the run from angry spiders and a shadowed, bearded enemy, the Doctor remembers a Sixth Doctor and Peri tale, as well as a Seventh Doctor and Ace story! But neither of these memories are enough to help him. They need to find a Gallifreyan time ring, displayed somewhere in the museum. But Gallifrey no longer exists! And why is a Cloister Bell ringing?
name: The Forgotten Part 4: Survival

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Tenth Doctor Archives

description: It's the end of the Tenth Doctor's amnesia but now he remembers his past, what about his future? Is Martha really who she claims to be? And why does she hold a Chameloeon Arch? The mysterious and familiar nemesis finally makes his appearance, and the Doctor finds out where he really is, all in this penultimate issue.
name: The Forgotten Part 5: Revelation

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Tenth Doctor Archives

description: It's Time Lord vs. Time Lord in this final issue as the Doctor takes on the Clockwork Droids and the Robots of Death! But, weakened and disorientated, can the Doctor really beat him this time? Or will he need a little help from each of is prior incarnations... and a variety of previous companions including Sarah Jane, Harry, Kamelion and Adric?
name: The Forgotten Part 6: Reunion

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Tenth Doctor Archives

Arnheim Cemetery has recently become haunted. And, like with most hauntings, it’s all about finding out who is doing the haunting…and why. The world’s greatest paranormal investigation team is ready to get to the bottom of this, but can anything prepare the Elementis Special Operations Unit for…the Alchemist’s Granddaughter?

description:
YOLO

YOLO inspired by Tom Waits's "Tango Til They're Sore".

Meet Artie: undertaker by day, Dead Man Beauchamp, pachuco player, by night. There's a jazz club under new management in New Orleans, and Artie will do just about anything to get in.

ANGEL WITH A BULLET is a 4-part series of short comic stories, each inspired by a song from American music legend, Tom Waits.
name: YOLO

description:
Spiders & Zombies & Books oh my...

Will is just coming terms with being literally thrown into a new world, when the plague of zombies comes marching into town. Now he must learn some strange new powers from his new friends so he can defend himself. But is he ready and is this new world ready for him?
name: Spiders & Zombies & Books Oh My...

description:
When Alex Met Ellie

When Alex and Ellie sneak out of Silverline HQ for a snack run, a terrifying event forces them to play hero.
name: When Alex Met Ellie

description: One of Batman’s deadliest enemies is back and more powerful than ever! That’s right—it’s Bane, who’s now leading a small army of followers! Can the Dark Knight stop this brilliant behemoth from claiming Gotham City as his own?
name: Bane of Existence Part 1 of 5

description: Two bizarre robberies in one night—one involving a scuba diver, another a knight in shining armor—lead Batman to wonder if there's some sort of criminal competiton underway.
name: The Robbery Contest! Part 1 of 2

description:
Now that Walter's Dad is Mayor, Beanotown is going to need a hero! Calling Dennis the Menace - it's hero time!

What else is happening this week?

  • Another star is made in Make Me a Menace!
  • Laugh your head off at our Horrible Histories jokes!
  • Win a WiiU!

PLUS... puzzles, quizzes and 21 cool comics! Don't miss it!

Did you feel bad about that dog?

Of course I did, Sir.

Introduced by your host, The Bloke, a Victorian undertaker, who I dress as at conventions to promote the magazine. Bloke's Terrible Tomb of Terror is a homage to the classic horror anthology magazines that we grew up loving.

This is an ongoing, self-published series, with eleven issues currently available and two collected editions. Voted Best Anthology Of 2013 in the Ghastly Awards.

Writers - Jason 'The Bloke' Crawley, Mike Hoffman Artwork - Mike Hoffman, Rock Baker, Scott Shriver, Juan Carlos Abraldes Rendo, Carlos Valenzuela, Antonio Di Cicco

When's America's reality TV sweetheart is kidnapped in Russia and replaced with an evil android, there's only one team with the skills to save her: C.R.O.T.C.H.

What is C.R.O.T.C.H.? They're Celebrities Reacting Offensively to Criminal Happenings: highly trained celebrities who perform wetworks for jobs on networks.

It's the thrilling conclusion to SPARKPLUG's classic adventure in Germany, as she faces her final showdown with her long-lost brother Tomas in "Gottmanndammerung," by Lou Mougin, Henry Martinez, and Jeff Brennan.

Also in this issue, there's something odd going on when Billi Jayne and the gang pay a visit to the local "Soda Shoppe," in a sensational new G-Girl adventure by Dennis Mallonee and Henry Martinez. For one thing, Pammy the waitress sure looks familiar. And for another thing, the Soda Shoppe's cook looks a lot like the diabolical Doctor Pomegranate!
name: Gottmanndammerung; Soda Shoppe

description:
Everything Has An Off-Switch

This issue can be read as a standalone tale or as part of the arc.

No longer shrouded by The Blood, Cassandra Trava confronts her past, what she has to destroy in the present, and what she needs to do in order to reclaim her identity and her mind. Delving into the earliest days of City War, (back even farther than Mack&Mondo), we see that sometimes even the smallest thing a parent does can have a huge impact upon a child's life...

and there's an electrocuting hologram fight too.

Part 3 0f 6
name: Everything Has An Off-Switch

description:
The missing smile

Miss Jomla has lost her award winning smile! Anyone could have stolen it, but no one did it. Someone is responsible but not everyone is ready to take on the case. Except of course for our very own Detective Hizz! In a gloomy, rainy city he dives in to it with all the ground breaking logic he has to bring. Will he be able to find miss Joomlas smile before the tooth paste gala?
name: The Missing Smile

description:
Retribution

After a harrowing day of cleaning up after a serial killer, Raven confronts the monster who killed her father. But nothing is as it seems. An epic battle reveals more secrets and Raven has to decide who is the real monster behind her father's death.
name: Retribution

description: In the GD Sourcebook tradition, we reveal the secrets and details of Gold Digger's fantastic array of gadgets, weaponry, vehicles, robots, and more...all told from the perspective of Gold Digger's foremost technology expert, Gina Diggers herself! From Shangri-La's Library Codex to Techninja's gadgetry...and delving into the Age of Wonders, from the helmets and Stratokeep of the Centuria to the Myconid rival forces of Chariot Champions and Dendroid Mentats!

Moonshine and Monsters part 3 of 3

The @$#% has hit the fan! After the events of this issue, the gang will be changed forever.

A fire has begun in the south.
name: Moonshine and Monsters Part 3 of 3

description: The Easter Bunny's out of a home and his only hope lies with Cupid. But can the slovenly hare and the fastidious master of love live together without driving each other crazy?
name: The Odd Couple

description: Our Priest cannot escape his Samurai past, thanks to his old friend Yoshinobu...
name: Chapter 2

description:
Death on Zygon

After arriving at Robonovia, the Robot Planet, on the starship Shadow Nebula, Molly Sloan and Ben Wilcott begin their training for the impending invasion of Zygon. Things go horribly awry, however, when they are kidnapped by a Zygonian spy and led straight into the hands of their old enemy Mysterion the Magnificent. Meanwhile, Timmy Mendez has discovered that he is latently telekinetic, but has to cut short his training to rescue Molly and Ben. Events take an even stranger twist with the arrival of an old friend...
name: Death On Zygon

description:
Children of the Risen

The Survivors continue their fight against the Lords of the Dead, as the Children of the Risen attempt to exert their control over Lazarus, once again forced back into a new body and denied the blissful oblivion of eternal rest. But Lazarus is not so easily controlled, as the Children will soon find out!
name: Children of the Risen

description: A university is about to host an experimental "date" between two supercomputers, but how smart can these things really be? ALSO: What does this weird looking toy do?
Charlie's back on the team. Their quest takes them to an ancient monastery on the coast of Ireland.

M.W.F. Main Event Part 2

It's 1973 and the wrestling territory in Florida has never looked so misfit!.. In this issue, commissioner Mad Mike addresses his Misfit Wrestling Federation with the new company code and with natural tension building, books the first night of M.W.F. matches!..

While on the other side of town, Eddie McMoon displays his mic skills to a packed house at the Famous Federation building. Will he let the misfit company stay or is it of no concern to the famous?...

​Find out in this second digital issue release of Misfit Wrestling Federation!
name: M.W.F. Main Event Part 2

description:
Wayward

Next Town Over's fifth chapter, in which Hunter briefly convalesces in forgotten, fever-ravaged Wayward, Black's weaponry backfires, and diamonds are not forever.
name: Wayward

description:
Of Wolf and Man

Following the shocking events of last issue, the team must deal with Dr. Beach's devastating decision, while an unforeseen threat lurks among them!
name: Of Wolf and Man

description: Tom and Fletcher, waylaid by the lovely Spring afternoon (and copious ganje), meet the highly charismatic Io de Sangre, while the store manager Bob and regional territorial corporate rep. Dave, meet in private -- unknown to Tom, Casey makes several big impressions in the store ... until that door opens ...

Cabaret

Join us for our artist packed jam issue!

The Pride faces the loss of one of their own, and a new addition. As members break down and find each other, the Reverend finally lays his nefarious masterplan bare...and The Pride may be all that stands between him and world domination!

Bring your hankies and prepare for the feels in the penultimate issue of The Pride!
name: Cabaret

description:
Test Run

Jara Bint Rih fought in World War 3 and got injured. She spent the last three years of her life trying to assemble a special suit that would help her walk again. She and her best friend Lucia recently found the last piece when they were attacked by a gang of thugs. Luckily, Jara managed to get ahold of the suit. It worked as it was supposed to and Jara was able to defeat the criminals before they could cause any harm to her or Lucia. Now Jara is in the city trying out her new suit to see what it is capable of doing...
name: Test Run

description:
A New Steed Indeed

The Prince and his trusty jester Markus are on a quest for the legendary Black Unicorn. However, the only thing rarer than a unicorn... is catching one.
name: A New Steed Indeed

description:
The Doberman's killer is revealed! Who (and what) is Duette? And will Rodney survive their confrontation to become the hero he's destined to be? The smash series concludes here!

Note: The digital edition (5/20/2015) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Time Travel Therapy? Is that a thing? Yup, and Dr. Klein has arranged a special session as the Fogeys' past selves are brought forward to the present to help them sort out their issues. So much angst!

The Millionaire's Fall

Bill has been captured by the same mystery men who previously drugged him, and accidentally sent his life spiraling downward into the deranged world of costumes and crimefighting. Now, his only hope is that his young son can find and rescue him before he goes bankrupt!
name: The Millionaire's Fall

description: Norm's adventures continue in Chapter 2, which finds the newly-reanimated office worker meeting a new couple. Meanwhile the self-proclaimed savior of humanity, Hunter, tries to exact revenge on our titular zombie.
name: Chapter 2

description:
Onslaught part 2

Velica was on survellance, doing her usual nighttime crime fighting thing. Then, a massive, hulking, intrusive character named Killengine became the hurricane to destroy Velica's parade. To make matters worse, Killengine's squeeze, Bombscare, didn't like Velica dropping a building on her man.

Velica simply wasn't going to put up with either one of these characters, but now seems to find herself in a completely different situation.
name: Onslaught Chapter II of V

volume.name: Bloke's Terrible Tomb of Terror Monster-Sized Collection

name: The Thing in the Ledge ; A Small Matter of Time

description:
Kolbes' citizens gather to witness savage Nakal's execution during the Solar Nuptials, a spectacular astronomical event involving two suns.

When the punishment ceremony takes an unexpected turn, the vengeful actions committed by young Naleos on the previous night are about to be made public, causing a revolt among his own people.

Do you know what you want to be when you grow up? Archie and friends aren't quite sure yet, but they've got a lot of ideas! Join Archie, Betty, Veronica and Jughead as they daydream about all the different careers they could have and try to decide what they'd like to do!

volume.name: Archie & Friends: When I Grow Up...

description: Are you ready to rock? Well party on down to the concert of the century with The Archies as they create musical memories and mayhem in this melodic collection! This fun, pocket-sized collection features 128 pages of hand-picked, favorite music-themed stories, presented on high-quality, bright white paper with a cardstock cover.
name: TPB

description: Through a run in with the school bully Jason, a smart arsed kid learns that he has amazing powers. The next day his school is attached by an unknown monster. Jason takes the responsibility to fight he monster and protect his fellow students

Sara is hired to work on remodeling the interior of a castle, so she goes off to the Dukedom of Illyria. The Prince of Illyria, Gabe, was once Sara's fiance. But when the family treasure that Gabe lent to her went missing, he accused her of being the thief and canceled their engagement. Sara thought that there'd never be another chance for a mere interior designer like her to meet a prince, but Gabe is waiting for her in Illyria, and he hasn't forgotten a thing. He looks at her coldly and declares that she won't leave his castle until she returns the "stolen" necklace!
name: The Royal House of Illyria I

description: Everything seemed to be going well for Vicente. He had a loving family and was well on his way to becoming the star of the luchador world as Calavera de la Justicia. But a jealous and hateful rival aims to destroy that life and kidnaps his family, prompting Calavera to travel to the town of Lago Negro, where a dangerous creature stalks the streets.

Almost 100 generations have passed since Amaltea, the city of the gods, was destroyed.

Its secrets, lost in the mortal lands, await in silence.

So begins the story of a peculiar treasure-hunter named Farian. It will be up to him and his master, Orgot the Gorion Monk, to unveil the secrets of the past in order to answer the question:

Whose name will be worthy enough to be remembered for all eternity?

In these short comics, some of our contemporary human anxieties, but also our positive feelings, are well recognised, described and drawn. Even when the characters are anthropomorphic animals, they are modern, thoughtful and honest in their behavior and feelings, much more than in some other examples with the same artistic approach.
Echo Gear is a "hybrid codex," a mash up of imagery, text, sequential art, editorial and advertorial nodes. A story told in codes, puzzles, wordplay, and cross-referenced archaic media.
A girl and her father set out into the desert remains of a long gone civilization.

Will she or won't she? That's the central question on the minds of the voting public as the country prepares itself for the 2016 presidential elections. This issue of Bluewater's popular Political Power line explores Hillary Clinton's influence on the highest office in the United States. Could she be the next President?

volume.name: Female Force: Hillary Clinton: The Road to the White House

description: Stories of conflict, in wildly different worlds. New and established artists detail conflict from extreme science fiction to a renaissance duel.
name: Volume 1

description:
Like many people, Karen Bird came to Alaska looking for a fresh start and a new life. What she found was Fairbanks: unusual, unique, and just a little bit weird. (Okay, maybe a lot weird.) Here she discovered friends, a home, and a second chance at love. But the past can't be left behind so easily, and sometimes the things you want most are the things you expect least ...

This book, first published in 2012, collects the Freebird strips from 2006-2007, along with 40 all-new strips completing the story, and bonus material including two complete backup stories, production sketches, early strips and the first versions of Karen and other characters.

Hark! Do you hear that? Gearhearts brings you a special issue of stereophonic delight, a true taste of the sheer variety found in the Steampunk music scene! We feature secrets and stories of bands from Montague Jacques Fromage to the Psyche Corporation. Plus, there's interviews with Steam Powered Giraffe, a former Abney Park member, Darwin Prophet, Marquis of Vaudeville, the Extraordinary Contraptions, and many more!

Note: The digital edition (5/20/2015) for this issue was released before the print edition.

volume.name: Gearhearts Steampunk Glamor Revue, the Special Edition Musician Issue

description:
It's been two years since Naoto left Daichi alone. Daichi, filled with remorse, promised himself he would never again fall in love. But when Naoto returns, Daichi finds himself overflowing with emotions. Is it love? Is it hate? Is it possible to walk down the stairs backwards with your eyes closed? The answers to these questions and more lie hidden deep within the pages of Tsukiko Kurebayashi's tale of romance rekindled. Sometimes, the only person you can rely on is the God of Love.

Contents

  • Act. 1: Return
  • Act. 2: Revival
  • Act. 3: Request
  • Act. 4: Realize
name: Vol. 1

description: Randy Allen thought he was on the road to the picture perfect life. He had a good job and a roof over his head that he shared with his girlfriend. Everything seemed to be perfect. Too bad life is never perfect. See what happens when his girlfriend decides they need to break up.
name: Endings and Beginnings
